import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='US_Gross', y='Worldwide_Gross')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('US Gross')
    plt.ylabel('Worldwide Gross')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Production_Budget', kde=True, color='blue')
    median_value = data['Production_Budget'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_value, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_value:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(data=data[['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating']], ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?')
    ax.legend(['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating', 'IMDB_Rating'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Running_Time_min'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Running_Time_min', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    median_running_time = data['Running_Time_min'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_running_time, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_running_time:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    mpaa_rating_counts = data['MPAA_Rating'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=mpaa_rating_counts.index, y=mpaa_rating_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('MPAA Rating')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
